article.headline: Toledo 95, Siena 71
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Keith Triplett scored 22 points and Sammy Villegas and Justin Ingram added 18 points apiece to lead Toledo over Siena 95-71 Wednesday night. Toledo (5-0) closed the first half on a 21-5 run for a 38-24 halftime lead. Triplett scored 16 of his points before the break. The Rockets pulled away from Siena in the second half, shooting 68 percent from the floor (73 percent on 3-pointers). Toledo outrebounded Siena 40-27 for the game. Tommy Mitchell led the Saints (3-4) with 16 points and three steals, while Michael Haddix had 15 points and Austin Andrews 12.
